      "text": {
        "arabic": "كَانَ الرَّجُلُ إِذَا أَسْلَمَ عَلَّمَهُ النَّبيُّ صلى الله عليه وسلم الصَّلاَةَ ثُمَّ أَمَرَهُ أَنْ يَدْعُوَ بِهَؤُلاَءِ الْكَلِمَاتِ: (اللَّهُمَّ اغْفِرِ لِي، وَارْحَمْنِي، وَاهْدِنِي، وَعَافِنِي وَارْزُقْنِي)",
        "transliteration": "Whenever anyone accepted Islam, the Prophet (ﷺ) used to teach him how to\npray then he would instruct him to invoke Allah with the following words:\nAllāhummaghfir lī, warḥamnī, waḥdinī, wa `āfinī warzuqnī.",
        "translations": {
          "en": "Whenever anyone accepted Islam, the Prophet (ﷺ) used to teach him how to pray then he would instruct him to invoke Allah with the following words:\n\nO Allah forgive me, and have mercy on me and guide me and give me good health and provide for me."
        }
      },
      "reference": "Muslim 4/2073, and in one of Muslim's reports there is the addition: 'For\nthese words combine [the goodness of] this world and the next.'",
